post_text:
The Jazz Combo from The University of Hartford's Hartt School of Music held a concert for our students today at CRHS.

The concert assembly is part of an outreach initiative by The Newport Jazz Festival whose goal is educating younger audiences on the history of jazz music. Students learned about jazz from its roots in New Orleans in the early 1900's through today's modern jazz music while celebrating Black History Month and the achievements of many African-American artists.

RSD 13's art teachers attended yesterday's Professional Development at the British Museum and Yale Art Gallery.
The teachers explored visual thinking strategies through objective/subjective critiques and comparisons with a docent-led tour. They also explored the museum through self-led tours and discussed art and history while making connections to their current practices at RSD 13.

post_text:
In honor of Veterans Day, Strong School students and staff joined Durham's annual Veterans Day celebration on the Town Green yesterday. Members of the Strong School Student Senate shared in the reading of the history of Veterans Day, the 8th grade ensemble played the National Anthem, and multiple 7th and 8th grade students shared information about relatives who have or are currently serving.

Memorial Middle School also honored Veterans by holding a student run assembly where students spoke about the importance of letters to and from home during different conflicts. Mr. Currlin and Mr. Glick spoke of their experiences in Vietnam, and the Boy Scouts presented the colors and raised and lowered the flag in honor of the Veterans that we celebrated yesterday.

post_text: The Summer Learning Open House was held this week at Brewster Elementary. Stations were set up for student engagement with information on all of the summer learning opportunities available. Drew the Dragon also made a surprise visit! Our book station offered each child a book to take home and read over the summer. The tech station allowed families to register for the Seesaw app so they can post and share their summer adventures with fellow students. The math station had math manipulates for students to see all the ways math is around them during the summer. Children could also sign their names on the chalk wall and received a Popsicle after guessing Drew's favorite number! Families can access all of our summer learning adventures on the RSD13 website at www.rsd13ct.org.

post_text: Yesterday, the Coginchaug Senior Class partook in a service day, where they met with the Superintendent, Dr. Veronesi, and First Selectmen, Laura Francis and Ed Bailey, to learn how they could lend a hand with various projects throughout the community. They completed trail work to remove invasive species at Brewster Elementary; participated in painting, gardening, and planting projects at Peckham Park; and tackled cleanup work at Lake Beseck. #rsd13ct

post_text: We've had a week filled with exciting activities for the students in our district. Yesterday, author Suzy Kline signed books for students at John Lyman School. She met with the Literary Board to discuss the writing process and also had lunch with a small group of students who wrote her letters. She ended her day with a wonderful and engaging large group assembly. Thank you so much for visiting our students, Suzy!

post_text:
Regional School District prides itself on being a strong community partner. We are happy to help publicize events and activities of interest to our staff and students. Flyers will be placed in a publicly-accessible Google Drive folder linked on our website and also posted prominently on the district Facebook page.

Community groups wishing to submit a flyer for review and posting should prepare an electronic version (PDF format is preferable) and send it to flyers@rsd13.org. Flyers or announcements submitted via other means may not be distributed.

Flyers will be reviewed and posted twice a month. Unfortunately, we cannot honor requests to re-distribute flyers or send out reminder notices.
